A bunch of family (parents, aunts / uncles, etc) are planning to go to Jamaica this year to celebrate my one Aunt's wedding
Originally the plan was to have the wedding there, but COVID.
Meanwhile, I'm just like, "I have 0 interest in flying to Jamaica."
Hopefully they don't force you into going
My plane ticket in particular is a kind that can be returned for the full cost up to a certain point
But they keep talking about Jamaica, and discussing the things available there
But I get absolutely zero excitement or interest
Apparently the hotel we'll be staying at has a nice pool, a really big one that even has a swim-up bar, as well as a bunch of other bars scattered around the property
But 1) I drink VERY modestly.  It's generally 1 drink per few months and 2) I'm a combination of 80+ lbs overweight and pale af.  So a trip to a tropical island isn't my cup of tea.
I like the more natural part of tropical vacations, tbh.
but yeah sometimes being resort-bound is a bit of a drag
the amenities are amazing, but tourist-trappy
there are honestly though some destinations you wouldn't want to wander depending on suroundings
but you don't always get the sense of a place in resorts
maybe gravitating toward national parks or preserves is a good strategy
I do advocate for travel though in general, it's priceless experiences, but the timing is still a bit nerve-wracking
